        "timestamp": "2019-02-15 14:57:46.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 3:\n\n> (6 comments)\n > \n > Thanks a lot.\n > Although many comments, I think the commit is good.\n > I do feel the mixed state of workflows from DB and SO is confusing\n > and brings a complexity we will not need once dev is completed. I\n > encourage putting a toggle already on this stage of dev.\n > If the toggle is on front-end or back-end -- both is legit.\n > \n > Please let know if you want any guidance with the feature toggles\n > mechanism.\n\n\nSome changes regarding to your comments were already made, some will do in next week. I have got also next review prepared but not submitted yet and I think I will wait till we merge this one.\n\nNot sure whether the toggle are really needed cause all the calls to the workflow services are being made asynchronous and shouldnt broke current functionality (only new entry in the console that it couldnt get the correct response from SO should appear). Of course if you insist not to have both calls in same time we can plan to make the feature toggle as well - we can discuss this topic on the next weekly.",
        "patchset_number": 3
